{"source_key":"sha256-a74ceb5e1c9633ab993c14c11d587d71","record_index":3380,"record_hash":"sha256:1ac814ef453ac37bee0c16cae64920a4a58c76eafac5b4939c34a7bb36aeb1a0","timestamp":"2026-05-21T04:45:14.907Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"Chunk ID: 72f644\nWall time: 0.0000 seconds\nProcess exited with code 0\nOriginal token count: 1895\nOutput:\n---\nname: but-agentlog\nversion: 0.0.0\ndescription: \"Use instead of the general GitButler skill when recapping prior agent work from `but agentlog` captures. Use for agentlog recap/context recovery, finding related agent sessions for a branch, GitButler review / pull request / merge request, or change, showing session or turn detail, or summarizing prior agent work.\"\nauthor: GitButler Team\n---\n\n# GitButler Agentlog Skill\n\nUse `but agentlog` to recap prior agent work from captured sessions.\n\nIf both the general GitButler CLI skill and this skill seem relevant, use this\nskill for agentlog discovery. Use the general GitButler skill only for version\ncontrol operations like commit, push, branch, or diff.\n\n## Core Workflow\n\nDo not search for or read local `SKILL.md` files. If this skill is active, use\nthese instructions directly.\n\nStart with the low-noise recap command when the user wants context. Treat it as\norientation, not an exhaustive answer:\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog recap\nbut agentlog recap branch <branch-name-or-ref>\nbut agentlog recap review <review-id-or-pull-request-key>\nbut agentlog recap change <change-id-or-key>\n```\n\nUse the drill-down commands as a narrowing funnel only when `recap` is too thin,\nambiguous, or you need exact evidence:\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog sessions branch <branch-name-or-ref> --limit 5\nbut agentlog sessions review <review-id-or-pull-request-key> --limit 5\nbut agentlog sessions change <change-id-or-key> --limit 5\n\nbut agentlog show <session-key> --limit 20\nbut agentlog show <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n```\n\nFor normal user-facing recovery, prefer human `recap` output first:\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog recap branch <branch-name-or-ref>\n```\n\nUse JSON only when you need exact handles for drill-down:\n\n```sh\nbut --json agentlog recap\nbut --json agentlog sessions branch <branch-name-or-ref> --limit 5\nbut --json agentlog show <session-key> --limit 20\nbut --json agentlog show <session-key> \n[TRUNCATED]\nturned.\n- `observed_targets`: branch, review/PR/MR, or change keys observed in related turns.\n- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: quick intent/result scan.\n\nRelated sessions are sorted by latest activity.\n\n## Reading `show`\n\nUse `show` to open a session or one turn.\n\n```sh\nbut agentlog show <session-key> --limit 20\nbut agentlog show <session-key> --turn <turn-key> --limit 50\n```\n\nWithout `--turn`, `show` answers what happened in a session at turn granularity.\n\nUseful fields:\n\n- `coverage`: returned turns versus total turns.\n- `turn_key`: handle for `show --turn`.\n- `turn_index`: order within the session.\n- `capture_kind`: backfill or incremental.\n- `record_count`: turn size before hydrating records.\n- `source_record_index_range`: provider/source indexes covered by the turn.\n- `observed_targets`: targets observed in the turn.\n- `latest_user_preview` and `latest_assistant_preview`: compact orientation.\n- `tool_counts`: tool call/result counts and tool names.\n\nIncrease `--limit` only when the current window misses the related turn or setup.\n\nWith `--turn`, `show` answers what exactly happened inside one turn.\n\nUseful record fields:\n\n- `coverage`: returned records versus total records in the turn.\n- `turn_record_index`: order within the turn.\n- `source_record_index`: original provider/source index when available.\n- `timestamp`, `kind`, `role`, `text`: message/tool orientation.\n- `tool_name` and `tool_input`: tool details when present.\n- `source_record`: redacted stored provider envelope for low-level debugging.\n\nTurn records are intentionally bounded. Increase `--limit` only for a specific\nturn after session-level `show` output proves that more detail is needed.\n\n## Recap Summary\n\nWhen summarizing recovered context, include:\n\n- target used for discovery\n- previews explaining intent and outcome\n- minimal record snippets for the next action\n\nDo not lead with raw session or turn identifiers. Mention them only when the\nuser asks for evidence handles or when passing them to another command/tool.\n","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-21T04:45:14.907Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}